<Author>Klamorris
<Content>So So.... We stayed here for one night just before taking a cruise from the Port of Miami. Here are the good points and bad pointsGood Points1- The rooms are huge and there are sitting areas and dining areas in the room.2- The room as also very clean3- The airport shuttle from MIA is free and we were able to get he shuttle to the port of Miami for $20 flat fee...they also only charge $5 to be tranported anywhere within I believe 10 miles of the hotelBad Points1- Not that I had planned to take one, but if I did, there was no bath tub in the bathroom...very wierd2- I have stayed at many Radisson hotels and they are well known for the great free breakfasts that they provide in their restaurants.....not continental either...this one for some reason did not have that.3- In every hotel I have ever stayed at, I was always allowed the option of early check in...regardless of the time I got there....we had to wait 3 hours for our room....check in was at 3PM and check out was at 11AM...for some reason our room was not ready until about 12:30PM...which in my opinion is totally unacceptable when like I said check out was at 11AM 
